{
    "directions": [
        "Preheat oven to 160\u00b0C (325\u00b0F). Place the ricotta, cream cheese, egg, lemon juice, vanilla, rice flour and sugar in a food processor and process until smooth. Spoon the mixture into a 20cm x 30cm slice tin lined with non-stick baking paper. Bake for 20 minutes or until firm. Refrigerate until cold. Top with fresh berries to serve."
    ],
    "ingredients": [
        "400g ricotta",
        "125g reduced-fat cream cheese",
        "2 eggs",
        "1/4 cup (60ml) lemon juice",
        "2 teaspoons vanilla extract",
        "1 tablespoon rice flour",
        "1/2 cup (110g) caster (superfine) sugar",
        "Fresh berries, to serve"
    ],
